metadata.name: BEHIND SILENCE
metadata.description:
| BEHIND SILENCE |

I am not a yeller ,
But pain builds up in me,
You might see me smiling,
But I am screaming deep beneath,
I keep my mouth shut,
Finding silence as the key,
Locking some emotions that may harm if free,
Donâ€™t try to dig deep in me as fire may burn you too,
Let me burn alone far inside,
as my soul is now used to.
